deck: A very, very weak Purifier that sues Bailey Hoskins and Xavier's School.
description:
Origin

Mr. Felworth apparently suffered mental trauma from his Uncle Garth, to the point that anyone that resembles Uncle Garth causes Mr. Felworth to experience extreme anxiety. At some point, Mr. Felworth joins the Purifiers.

Creation

Written by Max Bemis and drawn by Michael Walsh.

Major Story Arcs

The Purifiers attack Xavier's School but get worked. Mr. Felworth sees that he stands no chance in the fight and flees the battle. Bailey Hoskins, as a way to prove his worth, chases him down and confronts him. Mr. Felworth notes that Bailey looks like his Uncle Garth and immediately loses control of his bodily functions. He weeps and soils himself, spoiling Bailey's attempt at helping his team.

Due to the utter humiliation Mr. Felworth suffered at Bailey's hands, Mr. Felworth sues Bailey. Since Xavier's School has taken charge of Bailey, it has to pay the settlement amount, which is substantial.
name: Mr. Felworth

deck: Mike is a friend of Mr. Immortal. Mr. I asked Mike to bury him for a year so that he could have time alone to sort out his life.
description: After Mr. Immortal's breakup with Big Bertha due to his alcoholism, Mr. Immortal asked Mike to bury him for at least a year so that he could have some time alone to figure out what he wanted out of his life. Mr. I even told Mike not to let him up no matter what he said. Mike would bring him water every week which he filtered down to him through a pipe stuck through the ground. Although, Mr. I and Mike count each other as friends, Mike is not very patient as he does not wait long before pouring the water after alerting Mr. Immortal, nor does he stay around to talk.
name: Mike

deck: Jen was Bertha Crawford's agent when she became a plus-size model. Jen was fired when she revealed herself to be working for Dr. Nod.
description: Jen became Bertha Crawford's agent when Bertha became a plus-size model and had to start from the bottom again. Jen had scheduled a photo shoot for Bertha one night at Corktown Meats. The photo shoot was for a dietary supplement created by Dr. Nod. It would be a 24-hour diet pill and they wanted Bertha for the before and after shots. What really was going on was a trap set for Bertha and Jen was in on it. When Bertha received a phone call on her cell, she asked for a break and stepped outside. She overheard Dr. Nod speaking to someone about her, she made a sound and Dr. Nod started shooting at her. Bertha tore the door off the wall to save Jen but before she could get away, Jen injected her with a tranquilizer in the back of her neck. Later, Jen was present with Dr. Nod and the rest of the Bod Squad when Bertha woke up and was released. Jen had taken a pill that was a distilled mixture of Bertha's DNA and Mutant Growth Hormone which allowed her the same abilities as Bertha. Jen and Bertha fought for a short time before Jen was knocked out.
name: Jen

teams.name: Dr. Nod and the Bod Squad
